<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer6367472341777684282">Date of Birth: 1958<br/><br/>Tony Horwitz was a Pulitzer Prize-winning journalist and author whose books include Blue Latitudes, Confederates In The Attic and Baghdad Without A Map. His most recent work, published in May 2019, is Spying on the South, which follows Frederick Law Olmsted&apos;s travels from the Potomac to the Rio Grande as an undercover correspondent in the 1850s. <br/> Tony was also president of the S</span>
  <span id="freeText6367472341777684282" style="display:none">Date of Birth: 1958<br /><br />Tony Horwitz was a Pulitzer Prize-winning journalist and author whose books include Blue Latitudes, Confederates In The Attic and Baghdad Without A Map. His most recent work, published in May 2019, is Spying on the South, which follows Frederick Law Olmsted's travels from the Potomac to the Rio Grande as an undercover correspondent in the 1850s. <br /> Tony was also president of the Society of American Historians. He lived in Massachusetts with his wife, novelist Geraldine Brooks. <br /></span>
